  ('7abb0ba3-07c2-5d01-a35f-a1558409c56e', 'Home-Start Suffolk', 'Charity', 'Ipswich, Suffolk, IP5 3SL, Suffolk', 'Suffolk', 'https://www.homestartinsuffolk.org', 12, 786160, 'FY ending 2025-03-31; Charity Commission latest income', 5, 'Children and family services span casework, safeguarding, referrals and programme reporting. Community programmes involve volunteers, bookings, training registers and partner reporting.', 'Medium', '2026-06-24', 'primary', '', 'Chief Executive', 'headoffice@homestartinsuffolk.org', '01473 621104', 'https://register-of-charities.charitycommission.gov.uk/en/charity-search/-/charity-details/1105001/full-print', 'https://www.homestartinsuffolk.org', ARRAY['children','community'], ARRAY['children','community'], 'MEETING PREP — Home-Start Suffolk (Children, youth & families)

WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
Home-Start in Suffolk l believes that every parent should have the support they need to give their children the best possible start in life. Through our team of volunteers we provide support, friendship and practical help to any family who is going through a difficult time.The scheme also provides family group services.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
Ipswich, Suffolk, IP5 3SL, Suffolk, Suffolk. ~12 staff; income on record £786,160.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Blend: training + workflow review

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Children and family services span casework, safeguarding, referrals and programme reporting. Community programmes involve volunteers, bookings, training registers and partner reporting.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Youth charities often juggle CRM or case tools with heavy manual reporting to councils and funders. AI for programme summaries and parent communications is emerging but needs clear policy.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA is not the right lead for safeguarding case management — prioritise policy, training, and referral workflow clarity.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
Home-Start Suffolk shows children, youth & families delivery with material admin load — Cut grant reporting prep without changing your case system

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Cut grant reporting prep without changing your case system
• AI policy workshop for staff working with children and families
• Map referral and enrolment bottlenecks across programmes

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

