ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
M7 4TF, Greater Manchester, Greater Manchester. ~95 staff; income on record £10,846,986.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Blend: training + VA

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Registered charity with multi-programme delivery — likely admin load across casework, reporting and coordination.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Community charities often run on CRM-lite tools plus spreadsheets. AI training and virtual assistance for coordination frequently land well when tied to visible admin pain.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
If the need is primarily a new CRM, position VAxAI as review and support around existing tools rather than a platform replacement.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
ASSER BISHVIL FOUNDATION shows community & employment delivery with material admin load — Free up coordinator time across volunteers and bookings

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Free up coordinator time across volunteers and bookings
• Practical AI workshop for programme and outreach teams
• Review how reporting to funders is assembled each quarter

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
